{"questionId":"17489","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A small cuboid box has a rectangular base of length <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3x\">\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> cm and width <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> cm, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x > 0\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;The height is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> cm, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y > 0\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/ff847104e6a7c9e4bf868993a1172ebfe7180522.png\"></p>\n<p>The&nbsp;sum of the length, width and height is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"12\">\n  <mn>12</mn>\n</math></span> cm.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The volume of the box is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V\">\n  <mi>V</mi>\n</math></span> cm<sup>3</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Justify your answer.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach to explain that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V\"> <mi>V</mi> </math></span> is maximum when&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 2\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; attempt to find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{V''}\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>V</mi> <mo>″</mo> </msup> </mrow> </math></span>, sign chart (must be labelled <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{V'}\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>V</mi> <mo>′</mo> </msup> </mrow> </math></span>)</p>\n<p>correct value/s &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V''\\left( 2 \\right) = 72 - 72 \\times 2\"> <msup> <mi>V</mi> <mo>″</mo> </msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>72</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mn>72</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V'\\left( a \\right)\"> <msup> <mi>V</mi> <mo>′</mo> </msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; where&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a < 2\"> <mi>a</mi> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; <strong>and&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V'\\left( b \\right)\"> <msup> <mi>V</mi> <mo>′</mo> </msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>b</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span> where&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b > 2\"> <mi>b</mi> <mo>&gt;</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span></p>\n<p>correct reasoning&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V''\\left( 2 \\right) < 0\"> <msup> <mi>V</mi> <mo>″</mo> </msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mn>0</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{V'}\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>V</mi> <mo>′</mo> </msup> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; is positive for&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x < 2\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>and</strong> negative for&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x&nbsp;> 2\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>&gt;</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R1</strong></em> unless <em><strong>A1</strong></em> has been awarded.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V\"> <mi>V</mi> </math></span> is maximum when&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 2\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;N0</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17489","referenceCode":"19N.1.SL.TZ0.S_8d.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Justify your answer.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.7—The second derivative","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}